geneVariantDescriptions.description: NF2 Y66* results in a premature truncation of the Nf2 protein at amino acid 66 of 595 (UniProt.org). Y66* has not been biochemically characterized however, due to the effects of truncation mutations downstream of Q389 (PMID: 19910496, PMID: 31257748), is predicted to lead to a loss of Nf2 protein function.

references.title: Tumor-suppression functions of merlin are independent of its role as an organizer of the actin cytoskeleton in Schwann cells.
Expression of NF2 Modulates the Progression of BRAFV600E Mutated Thyroid Cancer Cells.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a clinical case study, a patient with melanoma harboring BRAF V600E developed progressive disease after 12 weeks of Tafinlar (dabrafenib) and Mekinist (trametinib) combination treatment, and progressed again after 106 weeks on anti-PD1 therapy including Opdivo (nivolumab) (90 weeks) followed by Keytruda (pembrolizumab), B2M V5Lfs*30, LRP1B W1344*, MAP2K2 F133L, NF2 Y66*, and TP53 C238F were identified in the post-progression biopsy in addition to BRAF V600E (PMID: 31082388).
